    <rdfs:comment rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string"
    >The concept of cohesion refers to relations of meaning that exist within the text, and that defines it as a text. Cohesion occurs where the interpretation of some element in the discourse dependent on that of another.

Odd speech, as manifested by at least two of the following six is one of DIAGNOSTIC CRITERIA FOR ASPERGER'S DISORDER (SZATMARI, ET AL. 1989)
1. abnormalities in inflection.
2. talks too much.
3. talks too little.
4. lack of cohesion to conversation.
5. idiosyncratic use of words.
6. repetitive patterns of speech.</rdfs:comment>
